    "feat": {
        "name": "Wandering Chef Dedication",
        "type": "stat_block_section",
        "subtype": "feat",
        "text": "Whether trained in a noble kitchen or a humble home, you know how to cook delicious dishes and source ingredients from the wilderness or urban settings. You become trained in Crafting; if you were already trained in Crafting, you instead become trained in a skill of your choice. You can use cookware instead of an alchemist\u2019s toolkit to craft alchemical foods. When using the Subsist downtime activity, you can use Crafting or Cooking Lore in place of Survival, and if you roll a failure, you get a success instead.  \n  \nYou gain the Quick Alchemy benefits, but can use it only to create consumables, and the consumables must be alchemical food. Any items you choose with Alchemical Crafting must be alchemical food, but they can be 1st level or 2nd level instead of only 1st level.   \n  \nYou create up to 4 versatile vials during your daily preparations. Typically, a wandering chef\u2019s versatile vials take the form of parcels of foraged ingredients.",
        "level": 2,
        "traits": [
            {
                "name": "Archetype",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 12,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
